    "gp_section_626145920014090803": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "f88ef51e1d163cb7209485f1be6f61f5e2dc804bc429af1b3de288f8590468a3_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg1L8VWthp__text": "7. What worked at 30 doesn’t work at 50 — and that’s okay.",
        "gg1R8B5603q_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0829/5330/6368/files/1_2.png",
        "gg4wsKf4aAe_text": "<p>As skin matures, it becomes thinner and more reactive. That 5-step routine you used to love? It might now be overwhelming your skin. Overexposure to too many actives or fragrances can lead to redness, sensitivity, or breakouts. The solution is&nbsp;not more — it’s smarter, simplified skincare. One well-formulated mask with targeted ingredients can do the job without stressing your skin barrier.</p>",
        "gg6WmeXBQ2L_text": "5. Layering multiple products can actually irritate aging skin.",
        "gg7hP4OYQZA_text": "<p>During perimenopause and menopause, estrogen levels drop. This impacts everything from collagen production to oil regulation and barrier strength. If your go-to products suddenly stop working, it’s not you — it’s your hormones. And your skincare should evolve alongside them.</p>",
        "gg8fJf_SZfH_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0829/5330/6368/files/8_edab28dd-87d3-4c0f-9ec9-9652cb1045d4.png",
        "ggDA-nvWEHj_label": "<p>Explore What Works for Your Skin</p>",
        "ggFaqI6AhAS_text": "<p>If you’re dealing with fine lines, dryness, or tired-looking skin, you must check out this brief yet crucial article before considering any other solutions.&nbsp;</p>",
        "ggH0u0HmQWs_text": "<p>If you’ve made it this far, you probably recognize some of these signs in your own routine. And no, it’s not your fault. The truth is, most skincare advice was never designed for women navigating the hormonal and structural changes that come after 45.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Supporting your skin at this stage is about&nbsp;<strong>working smarter</strong>, not harder.</p>",
        "ggIRvrUU3cx_text": "2. Your hormones are shifting more than your skincare routine is.",
        "ggKCZw73zNk_text": "<p>Starting in your 40s, your natural collagen declines rapidly. This causes skin to sag, thin, and lose that firm, “held together” feel. The problem? Most creams and serums only sit on the surface. Look for ingredients like hydrolyzed marine collagen that can absorb deeper and actually support your skin’s internal structure.</p>",
        "ggKm0dxeYXs_text": "3. Collagen loss accelerates — and most products can’t reach where it matters.",
        "ggMTtLiPXuX_text": "<p>By Clara Jensen</p><p>Last Updated: July 2025</p>",
        "ggNnQXGI-0__srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0829/5330/6368/files/2_1.png",
        "ggQ-G6myTs2_text": "6. Most masks aren’t designed for mature skin needs.",
        "ggUYRw8nmHu_text": "7 Reasons Your Skincare Stops Working As You Age — And How to Keep That 25-Year-Old Glow at 45",
        "ggWyGEnl6Qh_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0829/5330/6368/files/3_3c7c47dd-4bba-4004-ac61-0bd2e9663973.png",
        "ggYFAHu-kj8_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0829/5330/6368/files/5_1.png",
        "ggZHuYgoc8x_text": "1. Traditional skincare routines often ignore the real cause of aging skin.",
        "ggaOLwftTu1_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0829/5330/6368/files/6_1.png",
        "ggbL8oKeCJ1_text": "4. Dryness isn’t just dehydration — it’s a weakened skin barrier.",
        "ggctbi4yx8B_label": "<p>Explore Now</p>",
        "gggTy2IY0Ux_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0829/5330/6368/files/banner.png",
        "gggkZyRzBnu_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0829/5330/6368/files/3_1.png",
        "ggiFw0RxIWc_text": "<p>It starts with&nbsp;<strong>understanding what your skin actually needs</strong>—and giving it targeted care that goes beyond surface-level hydration.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>If your skin has felt dull, tired, or just not “you” lately, maybe it’s time to try something that meets you&nbsp;where you are.</p>",
        "ggiRYtMJJMK_text": "<p>Conventional sheet masks often prioritize scent, feel, or aesthetics—but not absorption. As skin ages, it requires products that can truly&nbsp;penetrate the barrier and deliver ingredients where they’re needed most. Thin, slippery masks may feel relaxing, but they rarely stay in place long enough to make a difference. For mature skin, what matters more is adherence, depth of delivery, and formulation that supports firmness and barrier repair.</p>",
        "ggsdxtqBRbP_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0829/5330/6368/files/Untitled_design_-_2023-07-12T200355.987.png",
        "ggsnA1sb7fR_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0829/5330/6368/files/1_1_83427607-bc93-486c-9c79-df29b276f5a8.png",
        "gguCnwVa854_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0829/5330/6368/files/Frame_1484580952_80c40562-ca10-49d4-9ebc-102373a42a14.png",
        "ggutrrXdMaM_text": "<p>Hormonal shifts thin out your skin’s outer layer, making it harder to lock in moisture. So even if you’re using hydrating products, your skin might still feel tight or flaky hours later. The fix? Ingredients like niacinamide and hyaluronic acid that don’t just add hydration — they rebuild your skin’s ability to hold onto it.</p>",
        "ggvDN5djePx_text": "<p>Most products focus on hydration, assuming that dryness is the only issue. But as we age, hormonal shifts—especially during perimenopause and menopause—cause a drop in collagen production and skin cell turnover. That means your skin needs more than just moisture. It needs structural support.</p>",
        "ggyr6lqtQdr_text": "<p>Skin evolves. It gets more reactive, thinner, and a little slower to bounce back. That doesn’t mean it’s “bad” — it just needs different care. You’re not doing anything wrong. You just haven’t been given the right tools. Until now.</p>",
        "section_preload": "true"
      },
